==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''tuple''' (''plural'' '''tuples''')

#{{settheory}} A [[finite]] [[sequence]] of [[term]]s; equivalently, an [[ordered]] [[set]].
#{{computing}} A [[single]] [[row]] in a [[relational database]].
#{{computing}} A [[set]] of [[comma]]-[[separated]] [[value]]s [[pass]]ed to a [[program]] or [[operating system]] as a [[parameter]] to a [[function call]].

====Synonyms====
*(''in set theory''): [[n-tuple]] (''when the sequence contains'' n ''terms''), [[ordered pair]] (''when the sequence contains exactly two terms''), [[triple]] ''or'' [[triplet]] (''when the sequence contains exactly three terms'')

